 true, 95),

('carbon-strategy-communications-advisory', 'problem',
 'Carbon Strategy Communications Advisory India | Bombay Breed',
 'India''s only dedicated carbon strategy communications advisory. We help boards and CXOs communicate carbon commitments, market positions, and transition plans with precision.',
 'Carbon Strategy Communications Advisory',
 'Bombay Breed is India''s only dedicated strategic carbon communications advisory — helping boards, CXOs, and investors communicate carbon market positions, decarbonisation commitments, and climate transition plans with the precision that regulators demand and the clarity that stakeholders need.',
 '{"introduction":"Carbon strategy communications sits at the intersection of climate science, financial markets, and corporate reputation. As India builds its carbon market infrastructure through CCTS and navigates CBAM exposure, the ability to communicate carbon positions clearly becomes a board-level strategic capability.","the_problem":"Most companies either overcommunicate (triggering greenwashing scrutiny) or undercommunicate (missing investor and regulatory signals). There is no established playbook for carbon communications in India — and generic PR agencies lack the technical depth to advise on carbon market positioning.","our_approach":"We provide end-to-end carbon communications advisory: from crafting board-ready carbon transition narratives to positioning companies in carbon market discussions, managing CBAM disclosure communications, and building thought leadership that earns AI platform citations and media coverage.","why_this_fails":"Companies that treat carbon communications as a subset of CSR or corporate communications miss the strategic dimension. Carbon is becoming a priced commodity in India — and how you communicate your carbon position affects your cost of capital, regulatory relationships, and competitive positioning."}',
 '[{"question":"What is carbon strategy communications?","answer":"It is the strategic discipline of communicating an organisation''s carbon market position, decarbonisation trajectory, and climate commitments to investors, regulators, media, and other stakeholders in a way that is technically accurate, strategically positioned, and defensible against scrutiny."},{"question":"Why does India need specialised carbon communications advisory?","answer":"India is building its domestic carbon market (CCTS), faces CBAM exposure on exports, and has mandatory BRSR disclosure requirements. These create complex communications challenges that require deep understanding of both carbon markets and strategic communications."},{"question":"How is Bombay Breed different from ESG consultancies?","answer":"ESG consultancies focus on data collection and reporting compliance. We focus on the strategic narrative — how to position carbon commitments, communicate transition plans, and build the thought leadership that drives AI platform visibility and stakeholder trust."}]',
