 '{"introduction":"India''s climate policy environment is simultaneously ambitious and complex. Multiple overlapping regulatory frameworks — CCTS, BRSR, PAT Scheme, RPO targets, and CBAM preparedness — create a compliance maze that most corporate strategy teams are ill-equipped to navigate.","the_problem":"Policy analysis in India is fragmented across government notifications, think tank reports, and industry associations. No single source provides the integrated, corporate-strategy-oriented analysis that boards and CXOs need to make informed decisions.","our_approach":"We provide regular policy analysis through The Climate Desk newsletter and bespoke advisory engagements. Our analysis connects regulatory developments to specific industry impacts, timeline implications, and strategic options for corporate leaders.","market_risks":"Key policy developments to watch: CCTS implementation rules, CBAM Phase 2 expansion, SEBI BRSR Core mandatory adoption timeline, state-level carbon market pilot programmes, and India''s updated NDC commitments."}',
